<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ900621-0125</DOCNO><DOCID>900621-0125.</DOCID><HL>   Financing Business:   Valhi Inc.</HL><DATE>06/21/90</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION</SO><CO>   VHI</CO><IN>BOND MARKET NEWS (BON)</IN><LP>   VALHI Inc., Dallas, has withdrawn its proposed publicoffering of $100 million in convertible subordinateddebentures due 2015, citing unfavorable market conditions.The preliminary prospectus was offered May 31, but asubsequent 10-day road show &quot;generated significant interest,but not at terms acceptable to us,&quot; a company executive said.Valhi, a holding company controlled by Dallas billionaireHarold Simmons, planned to use the proceeds to acceleraterepayment of debt maturing in 1994. But last week Moody'sInvestors Service Inc. assigned a single-B-3 credit rating tothe proposed debentures, saying its assessment of theproposal included its junior subordinated position and thesuperior position of hefty debt at the operating subsidiarylevel.</LP><TEXT/></DOC>